section.section:
"Participant" means an individual who is receiving supplemental foods or food instruments under the Program and includes:
Pregnant women;
Breast-feeding women up to 1 year postpartum who are breast-feeding their infants;
Postpartum women up to 6 months after termination of pregnancy;
Infants under 1 year of age; and
Children who are at least 1 year old but under the age of 5 years.

Upon presentation by the participant of a written request, including justification, a local agency may mail or otherwise deliver food instruments to an individual on the basis of the difficulty of the participant and the participant's proxies in obtaining the food instruments. The justification may include:
Illness;
Imminent childbirth;
Difficulty of access to the local agency; or
Handicapping condition.
